`user/atk_user.c:7-92`), a software renderer backing the `video_*` API (`user/video_surface.c:1-210`), and lightweight stubs for kernel-only host hooks (`user/atk_user_host_stub.c:1-48`) plus basic serial stand-ins (`user/serial_stub.c:1-24`).\n- Built the sample GUI app (`user/atk_demo.c:1-160`), which themes its own ATK state, renders into the software surface, and responds to `USER_ATK_EVENT_*` before calling `atk_user_present`. The design and usage are documented in `docs/user_atk.md:1-41`.\n- Added `atk_user_present` integration and ensured the remote `atk_image` can ingest the user-supplied buffer each frame (`user/atk_user.c:35-62`).\n\n**Testing**\n- `make build/bin/atk_demo` (builds all required user objects, links `atk_demo.elf`, and copies it into the FAT-backed `build/bin`; emits existing warnings about `NULL` being redefined in `include/types.h:19` and indentation warnings in `src/atk/util/jpeg.c:570/875`, which were already present).\n\n**Notes / Next Steps**\n- Shell now advertises the new `useratk` command and runs the ELF from `/bin`.\n- The JPEG decoder still raises misleading-indentation warnings and `types.h` redefines `NULL` when user sources include `<stddef.h>`; consider cleaning those up.\n- Copy `build/bin/atk_demo` (and `userdemo2`) into the data image as needed before booting, since `build/` acts as the FAT root.\n\nLet me know if youd like help wiring additional userland apps or trimming the outstanding warnings."}]}}
